pullRequest.body:
Split the 2300-line behemoth `OperatorNorm.lean` into 8 smaller files, of which the largest is 600 lines.

---
<!-- The text above the `---` will become the commit message when your
PR is merged. Please leave a blank newline before the `---`, otherwise
GitHub will format the text above it as a title.

To indicate co-authors, include lines at the bottom of the commit message
(that is, before the `---`) using the following format:

Co-authored-by: Author Name <author@email.com>

Any other comments you want to keep out of the PR commit should go
below the `---`, and placed outside this HTML comment, or else they
will be invisible to reviewers.

If this PR depends on other PRs, please list them below this comment,
using the following format:
- [ ] depends on: #abc [optional extra text]
- [ ] depends on: #xyz [optional extra text]
-->

This split was annoying to do since the existing file is very messy, with lots of nested sections / namespaces with their own local variables, and repeated swaps between implicit vs. explicit binding of variables. It is possible that there are some redundant `variable` declarations in some of the post-split files.

(NB: Please ignore the commit message of the first commit in this branch -- I backed those changes out when I realised it made more sense to split the file first. This PR contains no new code, and no changes to existing code except moving it from place to place.)

(So this extract gives an idea of how bad the original file had got!)
